item.title: History of Cesar Chavez Park
item.description: This place you’re sitting. Have you ever thought about it. Do you give much consideration to the places you visit? Have you ever noticed the Si Se Puede! Embossed on the concrete? What about the bust of a man that sometimes a little girl sells lemonade under while a man strolls by walking his cat? What is this place? What was this place? Well, you’re likely a parent keeping an eye on your children as they play on the Jungle Gym, so let’s start with this park.
